sql:
SELECT m.metric_id, m.standard_name
FROM metrics m
WHERE m.standard_name = 'air_temperature' AND m.updated_by = 'Alice Johnson';

SELECT metrics.standard_name, metrics.units, bety_references.reference_name
FROM metrics
JOIN bety_references ON metrics.bety_reference = bety_references.bety_id;

external_knowledge:
'K' is the unit symbol for Kelvin; 
Kelvin is a unit of temperature; 
Metrics measured in Kelvin are typically temperature metrics.
